HEADWORD: Photopsia
<hw>Pho*top"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>fw^s</grk>, <grk>fwto`s</grk>, light + <grk>'o`psis</grk>
sight.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An affection of the eye, in which
the patient perceives luminous rays, flashes, coruscations, etc. See
<er>phosphene</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

